parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high beam headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The high beams do not turn on
the high beam indicator light on the dashboard is illuminated but the exterior lights do not change
the high beams suddenly stop working without warning
the low beams work properly but the high beams do not.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected cracking or shattering of the windshield can cause a loss of visibility, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Small chips or cracks in the windshield that spread rapidly

and can occur even when the vehicle is stationary; windshields cracking or shattering without apparent cause; cracks or chips appearing in the windshield after minor impacts or with no visible signs of damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high beam headlights can reduce visibility, making it difficult to drive safely, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: High beams fail to turn on
with no indication of a problem; no warning lamps or messages appear prior to the failure.
